   "source": [
    "# Adaptive integration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(I, errest) = quadgk(f, 0, 4, atol = 1.0e-14, rtol = 1.0e-14) = (-2.825533373437446, 2.1510571102112408e-14)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f = x -> (x+1)^2*cos((2*x+1)/(x-4.3));\n",
    "\n",
    "using QuadGK\n",
    "@show I,errest = quadgk(f,0,4,atol=1e-14,rtol=1e-14);  # 'exact' value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We perform the integration and show the nodes selected underneath the curve."

    "tol_ = @. 10.0^(-4:-1:-14)\n",
    "err_ = zeros(size(tol_))\n",
    "num_ = zeros(Int,size(tol_))\n",
    "for i = 1:length(tol_)\n",
    "    Q,t = FNC.intadapt(f,0,4,tol_[i])\n",
    "    err_[i] = I - Q\n",
    "    num_[i] = length(t)\n",
    "end\n",
    "\n",
    "using DataFrames\n",
    "DataFrame(tol=tol_,error=err_,f_evals=num_)"

   "source": [
    "As you can see, even though the errors are not less than the estimates, the two columns decrease in tandem.
